reviews.review_text: Great Recording This is a stellar AUD recording.  I categorize all my AUD recordings by quality and this one goes into the highest rating.  I got about 100 SBD shows when they were still available and this is just as good as any.  Thanks to the taper and recording engineer.

Life is too short This starts out with a nice Stranger and it's a sweet audience tape but the setlist ... it blows.  Something about those early eighties shows, with a few exceptions ... workmanlike.  Probably fun to be there, but not very interesting the second time around.

Gotta love Other One I first heard The Other one from this show on David Gans's Deadhead Hour (yes, boys and girls, even back then).  It was the first time I heard what Bobby could do when completely unleashed.  It's one of my favorite TOOs of all-time.  I've had the SBD until now; while it's clearer, this AUD is excellent and has the live feel missing from the board.

Thank you Steve!
